title: Anchor House Foundation Ride for Runaways-Training
Juniors in the Jungle Mountain Bike Ride
Tour of Colts Neck.
course:
3.8 mile loop with one short hill per lap.
Rolling Closure.
Yellow Line Rule. No following vehicles. 
Rural/Suburban area.  Roads open to traffic.
registration:
Enter on Bike Reg or by mail to
 Atlantic Bicycle Club
P.O. Box 330, Allenwood, NJ. 08720
notes: All CUSA rules apply.  Juniors 9 to 14 years ride ALTERNATE course to all other racers. Safe neighborhood course.  No wait list for Cat. 5 event.  First race 8AM all others follow on completion of previous race. TANDEM race this year !!!
directions: Garden State Parkway to exit 109.  West on Rt. 520 for 1 1/4 miles.  LEFT on PHALANX Rd.  Go 2 miles to LAIRD Rd.  Make  RIGHT to registration 1/4 mile to ball field on left.   Registration opens 7/15 am.

Bob Riccio Memorial Tour de Pitman

Bob Riccio Memorial Tour de Pitman
123 mens pro race 50 miles
Presented by
The Caffeinated Cyclist
Pitman, NJ
Saturday, June 12, 2010

Approximate 3 mile loop with two rolling climbs. Start/Finish on Broadway in downtown Pitman. Mostly fresh pavement with a few bumps on the downhill to Broadway. Rolling closure during race  for safety  but:
 
YELLOW LINE RULE WILL BE ENFORCED

online Registration www.bikereg.com $40. pre reg $45.day of race.Online Registration Closes
Friday, June 11, 2010 at 12:00 NOON ET

directions:

title: Campmor H2H #4, The 15th Annual Bulldog Rump, AMBC
Freedom Tour
description:
The 2010 Freedom Tour Benefit Race.
To benifit the Long Hill Township Fire Department, First Aid Squad & Long Hill Police Explorers
course: Course is a flat criterium. Each lap is .9 mile. Mercer Street has been repaved this year.
registration:
Pre-registration at www.bikereg.com
Pre-registration must be postmarked by Monday, July 19th. Entries postmarked after July 19th must include $5 late fee. Make checks payable to Watchung Wheelmen. Same day registration closess 1/2 hour before posted start time. Filed limit Pro 125, Cat 4/5- 75 all others 100.
notes: Part of the course has been repaved. Mercer Street, the last street before coming onto the final straight was repaved in the fall.
directions: Exit 36 off of Rt 78. Head north towards BaskingRidge. Turn right at 4th traffic light. Registration and restrooms will be located behind the announcers stand on Main Ave.
